WeatherWise/
├── docs/
│   ├── FEATURES.md           # Brainstormed features
│   ├── MVP.md                # Selected MVP features
│   └── USER_STORIES.md       # User stories (optional if using GitHub Issues only)
├── src/
│   ├── __init__.py           # Makes 'src' a Python package (optional)
│   ├── main.py               # Entry point of the application (CLI or Flask 'app.py')
│   ├── weather_api.py        # Functions to call external weather API (OpenWeatherMap)
│   ├── db_manager.py         # Logic for storing city data (SQLite or JSON)
│   ├── cli_interface.py      # For CLI menus, if doing CLI version
│   ├── templates/            # (If using Flask) Holds HTML templates
│   │   └── index.html
│   └── static/               # (If using Flask) For CSS, images, etc.
├── tests/
│   └── test_weather_api.py   # Example of unit tests (if you have time to implement tests)
├── requirements.txt          # List of Python dependencies (requests, Flask, etc.)
├── .gitignore                # Git ignore file (e.g., venv, __pycache__, etc.)
└── README.md                 # Project overview, setup instructions, usage
